Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Roughly chop the @sundried tomatoes{30%.g}(roughly chopped). Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}(zested and halved). Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked from stalks and roughly chopped) and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can}(drained and rinsed).

Heat a splash of oil in a #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. When hot, add the red onion and sundried tomatoes. Add a splash of water, stir and cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Pour the @water{240%ml} into the saucepan along with the @vegetable stock powder{1}(stock powder) and @bulgur wheat{120%g}. Stir and bring to the boil. Stir in the chickpeas, bring back to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Pop a #lid{} on the saucepan. Remove from the heat and leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve the @premium tomato mix{125%.g}(halved). Trim the @courgette{1}. Use a #vegetable peeler{} to peel long ribbons from all sides of the length of the courgette. Stop when you get to the spongy centre (discard the centre). Pop the courgette ribbons in a #bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of @olive oil{} and a squeeze of lemon juice. Toss to dress the courgette and keep to one side.

When the bulgur wheat is cooked, remove the lid and stir through the fresh tomatoes and chopped mint. Add a pinch of lemon zest and a good squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and add more salt, pepper and lemon to taste.

Share the bulgur jumble between your #bowls{} and crumble over the @feta cheese{100%.g}(crumbled). Top with the @wild rocket{40%.g}(leaves) and a neatly arranged portion of courgette ribbons. Finish with a drizzle of olive oil. Enjoy!